 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukaiyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaiyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 9:00:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DISCUSSION - Our Reservation system</span><hr size=1> VS/Trakanon- High level people depend on VS to get their epics, those high level people's guilds need their members to have their epics so that they can move on in the world.  I believe that we wouldn't have this gridlock in one area, and a near complete lack of attention in an other area if we weren't reserving key mobs like VS.  Meaning that, while there are dozens of guilds on the VS rotation, how many people do you see lining up to kill the Vindicator?  Or to ravage the temple of Veeshan, etc...the reason for this is that since the amount of VS/Trak killings has been so spread out amongst guilds, guilds have to wait a longer amount of time to get the gear they need to move on to higher end areas.(be it epic quests pieces, or the necessary armor that tanks need to keep up with high end Velious mobs)  While they are waiting, more and more guilds are coming to power and joining the waiting list, making the wait that much longer.  If we just canned reservation on VS/Trakanon, then yes, lower level guilds would not have a  chance at him- but only for a little while.  Realistically, one of the current &quot;lower level&quot; guilds would probably miss no more than one shot on their rotation.  The waiting list is like what?  8 months or something.  It would NOT take all of the &quot;Uber&quot; guilds on the server 8 months to get the gear they need and move on from mobs like VS and Trakanon. (One big factor is that Uber guilds tend not to fail that often killing these mobs) This would in turn mean that there are less guilds wanting to kill these mobs, and thus freeing up some of the gridlock.    <br>
<br>
Vox/Nag- Remove indies, but allow guilds to reserve them, in order to give that guild the experience and gear they need to move on to higher end raids in the future.  There's nothing that says a current &quot;non-uber&quot; guild can't become uber in the future. =D<br>
<br>
