I agree with Ganon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 785<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/14/01 2:39:43 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://216.242.60.166/chicktourney_com/larges/415.jpg width=110 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DISCUSSION - Our Reservation system</span><hr size=1> Without reservations, most people will never be able to see some of these epic encounters.  Between LoH, SR, Enshadowed, Watchers, and maybe some other guilds, Trakanon/VS could be dead within only a few hours of him spawning.<br>
<br>
There are some people that have not been guild affiliated that could gather the required people for a raid somewhat &quot;easily&quot;.  Grrumble and Danni are people that stick out in my mind, and now Adune.  I think that everyone has just as much right to lead a raid as anyone else, regardless of guild tag.<br>
<br>
I think that Adun's idea he presented a while ago is good.  I'm not sure if this is exactly it, but this is what I think should be done:<br>
<br>
I propose that instead of a single person doing a reservation of an uber mob, you have 15 people doing the reservation, all under one raid leader.  If you are supporting the reservation of one epic mob, you can't be assisting in the reservation of another epic mob.  So, for example, if Kruunch (Just picked his name at random) wants to lead a VS raid, he and the 14 others that are supporting him are all acting as one person to reserve VS.  None of those 15 people may use their names to help reserve VS for another date until their raid is completed.  None of those 15 people may use their names to reserve other epic mobs until their raid is completed.  Perhaps having your name on 2 reservations is ok.  Dunno.<br>
<br>
This would allow anyone with enough preestablished support to reserve something, but you won't have the same group of people reserving epic mobs just under a different name.  You won't have the same 15 wizards all leading a VS raid as an independant all inviting each other.<br>
<br>
The result of this would be that SR could have about 2-3 reservations due to their population being about 40 people?, while a smaller guild of only about 20 people could only reserve 1 mob, and an independant can still run a raid, as long as they know enough people that have not yet committed to any raids yet.<br>
